dmenu - dynamic menu - personal fork
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Fork changes
------------
- personal changes
  + location (normal, center, cursor, {top,bottom}-{left,right})
  + font from env FONT_SIZE and FONT
  + bw colors
  + border color
  + disable border when managed
  + preselect -ve values
- patches
  + dmenu-bidi-20210723-b34d318.diff
  + dmenu-border-4.9.diff
  + dmenu-center-20200111-8cd37e1.diff
  + dmenu-linesbelowprompt-and-fullwidth-20211014.diff
  + dmenu-managed-4.9.diff
  + dmenu-mousesupport-5.1.diff
  + dmenu-password-4.7.diff
  + dmenu-preselect-20200513-db6093f.diff
  + dmenu-xyw-5.0.diff


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dmenu
-------------
See the man page for details.
